 charts and entire books to map your family history.","fullscreen":true,"importSrc":"http://www.toptenreviews.com/i/rev/scrn/small/49075-heredis-mac-x.24.jpg","src":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/YVFMNYwBqW7cgR4pnavwp6.jpg","credit":"","align":"","id":"YVFMNYwBqW7cgR4pnavwp6","mos":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/YVFMNYwBqW7cgR4pnavwp6.jpg","alt":""},"id":"07ed36b7-1006-4d41-9eb1-c89a26089d5e","type":"image"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["This program is a good choice if you like to share your genealogical research with family and friends. Using Wi-Fi and USB technology, you can sync with other Macs, iOS devices and PCs. It can recognize devices that plug directly into your computer. You can share your genealogy findings online or directly to other devices using a USB flash drive or external hard drive.","Heredis connects to Heredis Online, its own genealogy web search, and other popular genealogy search sites like FamilySearch, Ancestry and MyHeritage. This Mac genealogy software was able to correctly recognize GEDCOM files imported into the program. However, some of the data was misplaced and we had to reenter it into the proper data fields."]},"id":"fade5d86-d42b-46e4-b3dc-54bb9785bbd6","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Creating Connections"},"id":"e7c4fc91-42e4-4cbc-9a1f-f7bf6756a611","type":"heading"},{"data":{"path":"/NuS23SoLdtf7okhHKdcAW3.jpg","link":{"href":"","rel":null,"target":""},"caption":"Every family is different, so it&#39;s important to find family tree software that can list different types of blood and marriage relationships. The more accurately you enter data about your family history, the more accurate your published materials will be later. Heredis lists common child statuses like legitimate, illegitimate or adopted. You can also find less-common listings for people, including same-sex couples, unmarried and childless. By adding these descriptions to individuals, you give the software additional information, filling in the gaps so it doesn&#39;t prompt you to add a child for a childless or unmarried person later.","fullscreen":true,"importSrc":"http://www.toptenreviews.com/i/rev/scrn/small/49075-heredis-mac-x.27.jpg","src":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/NuS23SoLdtf7okhHKdcAW3.jpg","credit":"","align":"","id":"NuS23SoLdtf7okhHKdcAW3","mos":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/NuS23SoLdtf7okhHKdcAW3.jpg","alt":""},"id":"a939f60b-c0b8-4ad2-8b58-339366218b90","type":"image"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["DNA test results are another tool genealogists use to find the geographic origins in their ancestry. Genealogy software often lacks a DNA testing service, but many software packages provide a way for you to input the DNA test data you have. Unfortunately, Heredis lacks a tool for inputting DNA test data into the program.","To save time, Heredis has name and county pop-up tools that anticipate the name of a location or person before you finish typing. This is useful once you have a large database with common names. However, the software favors French spellings and adds accent marks automatically. This proves frustrating when the software generates the wrong name or spelling. You also have to be careful when selecting locations. Often, the first choice isn&#39;t the most obvious. For example, if you enter &#34;Brooklyn,&#34; the first pop-up appears as Brooklyn, New Zealand instead of Brooklyn, New York."]},"id":"3a00f6a1-1edf-4ada-b138-e673fc8a7876","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Charting Capabilities"},"id":"d560a4a4-2599-46d8-8802-a0d0d7959739","type":"heading"},{"data":{"path":"/6kPuEs7WX6VkTksGQTm3sM.jpg","link":{"href":"","rel":null,"target":""},"caption":"Heredis brings a lot to the table in terms of design. True to Mac software&#39;s eye for aesthetics, the publishing section provides bright, colorful themes for your charts. There are 45 themes available for your charts and 25 that you can apply to reports. When you design a chart, it imports your family data automatically, regardless of theme or chart type. The charting features are widely customizable. You can apply text editing and change the color and style of each family tree node.","fullscreen":true,"importSrc":"http://www.toptenreviews.com/i/rev/scrn/small/49075-heredis-mac-x.25.jpg","src":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/6kPuEs7WX6VkTksGQTm3sM.jpg","credit":"","align":"","id":"6kPuEs7WX6VkTksGQTm3sM","mos":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/6kPuEs7WX6VkTksGQTm3sM.jpg","alt":""},"id":"75a505b5-48d1-43af-80fa-31250c97c60d","type":"image"},{"data":{"text":"Citations &amp; Organization"},"id":"37e26dc2-112e-4218-97b9-786684ea3719","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["The program has an array of source categories like records, publications, correspondence, inscriptions, media, online or CD-ROM sources, and name lists like census or passenger lists. When adding sources, this Mac genealogy software provides fields for name, author, type of document, URL and email. Once you&#39;ve entered this information, Heredis formats the sources into accurate and correctly formatted citations.","The source tools in Heredis are fast and thorough, but the software is missing some useful tools like a soundex calculator seen in other programs. A soundex system encodes last names phonetically to group similar surnames. The calculator gathers these matching names, making it easier to group individuals with similar last names. Heredis also lacks a to-do list to help you organize your research, an especially useful tool when tackling lots of research or a large family database.","<strong>Help &amp; Support</strong>","Support for Heredis is mainly available online; the in-software support is non-existent. Any menu or help options in the software point to the manual, updates or support options on the website. There are no options for reaching customer support via phone or email. The user forums on the company&#39;s website are a good place to find constructive help, critique and research tips. The website has videos, data sheets, sample files and FAQs to answer your questions. You can find 97 pages of help content in the Mac and PC manuals, which are available online in a printable PDF format. The latest software updates to Heredis are available in the website&#39;s support section as well."]},"id":"726e7ee4-f62b-4c08-861d-6cb05389e09c","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"58ca2493-5300-4535-aeb8-89829b18c8ed","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["In Heredis, you can spruce up your family tree charts with the help of 45 well-designed templates and customization options. And for any unconventional relationships you may dig up in your family history, the variety of relationship types means fewer tangles or special notes down the line. The lack of a soundex calculator or task list requires more organization on your part, and the French-favoring predictive text means a little extra typing. While Heredis has a few quirks and lacks some helpful tools, like a way to input DNA test data, these flaws are not necessarily deal breakers."]},"id":"fd67c5f5-9990-4c39-b955-d23f953e1fc0","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_49103","url":"/heredis-mac-x-2-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"nicole-johnston","url":"/author/nicole-johnston","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"Nicole Johnston","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"nR6fcTbvfudgncYJbhzqDB","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2010-03-26T20:28:25Z","datePublished":"2010-03-26T20:28:25Z","name":"Heredis Mac 2015","synopsis":"For more than two decades, Heredis has developed one of the best genealogy programs for Mac and PC. This visually appealing software has the essentials with a logical layout.","review":{"rating":91,"verdict":"Heredis has minor quirks but remains solid genealogy software with a variety of useful features, including the ability to define uncommon relationships.","pros":["Heredis offers crisp, well-designed theme